During the photocatalytic degradation of MB, sacrifice agents EDTA⁃2Na and K2Cr2O7 were added respectively to capture photogenic h+ and e-.[

                              59

                           ] When EDTA⁃2Na was used as the sacrificial agent, MB could not be degraded; However, when we used K2Cr2O7, MB was rapidly degraded within 60 min (Fig. 10
                           ). It could be seen that h+ was the main active species in the photocatalytic process, and e− was the secondary active species.
